nana nana boo-boo, term to taunt others with what they cannot have. Nana nana boo boo is used to taunt others, especially other children, to express that they can't have what they may want. This can be used for children showing, but not sharing their food, toys, or other things. It can also be used when children are playing tag or chasing each other; the child who is winning and not being caught would taunt the other children by saying "nana nana boo-boo."
